Comment (main.go:532):
Dependency policies are evaluated by calling `EvaluatePolicies` once per dependency inside the dependency-gather callback. Since `EvaluatePolicies` already supports evaluating a slice of dependencies, this approach repeats policy processor setup (and potentially policy bundle loading) for each dependency, which can significantly increase runtime for repos with many dependencies. Consider gathering dependencies first and then calling `EvaluatePolicies` once with the full dependency slice, or refactoring `EvaluatePolicies` to expose a cheaper per-dependency evaluation path that avoids redoing shared setup each time.
